Questions:
1) STOR ACC, [address]
2) 109
3) An OPCODE would be needed for each new command. For compare, a new register and flags would be needed to store 
the intemediary steps. For PUSH and PULL, a new register with the memory location of the stack would be needed. Two's
compliment would only need the actual code for conversion.
4) Details on which operation is being done would need to be passed.

